  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Note: the governing requirement mandates experimental-validation as the primary verification method for output comparison; the supporting validation activity was conducted via numerical-simulation, which the assessment narrative characterises as functionally equivalent to bench testing given the high mesh resolution and validated turbulence model.",
